
     Instance vs Static Method — Easy Notes With Icons & Memory Allocation
🔷 1. Instance (Non-Static) Method
📌 Definition

An instance method belongs to an object.

👉 It works only after object creation using new.

✅ Example
class Student{

    int id = 101;                     // instance variable
    static String college = "ABC";   // static variable

    void show(){                     // instance method

        System.out.println(id);      
        System.out.println(college);

        display();
    }

    static void display(){
        System.out.println("Static Method");
    }
}
           🔹 Object Creation
           Student s1 = new Student();
            s1.show();
🔷 2. Instance Method Relationship
Feature	Allowed
🔹 Access Instance Variable	✅ YES
🔹 Call Instance Method	✅ YES
🔹 Access Static Variable	✅ YES
🔹 Call Static Method	✅ YES
🔷 3. Instance Method → Instance Method ✅
📌 Example
void show(){
    print();
}

void print(){
    System.out.println("Hello");
}
💡 Why?

✅ Object already exists
✅ Memory already allocated in Heap

🔷 4. Instance Method → Instance Variable ✅
📌 Example
int id = 10;

void show(){
    System.out.println(id);
}
💡 Why?

✅ id stored inside object memory
✅ Instance method also works with object

🔷 5. Instance Method → Static Method ✅
📌 Example
void show(){
    display();
}

static void display(){
    System.out.println("Static");
}
💡 Why?

✅ Static members already loaded in Method Area

🔷 6. Instance Method → Static Variable ✅
📌 Example
static int count = 100;

void show(){
    System.out.println(count);
}
💡 Why?

✅ Static variable shared by all objects

⭐ MAIN POINT OF INSTANCE METHOD
✅ Instance Method Can Access EVERYTHING
✅ Instance Variable
✅ Instance Method
✅ Static Variable
✅ Static Method
🔷 7. Static Method
📌 Definition

A static method belongs to the class, not object.

👉 No object needed.

📌 Example
class Demo{

    static void show(){
        System.out.println("Hello");
    }
}
🔹 Calling
Demo.show();
🔷 8. Static Method Relationship
Feature	Allowed
🔹 Access Instance Variable	❌ NO
🔹 Call Instance Method	❌ NO
🔹 Access Static Variable	✅ YES
🔹 Call Static Method	✅ YES
🔷 9. Static Method → Instance Method ❌
📌 Example
static void show(){
    print(); // ERROR
}

void print(){
}
💡 Why Error?

❌ Instance method needs object memory

But static method runs before object creation.

JVM asks:

“Which object should I use?”

🔷 10. Static Method → Instance Variable ❌
📌 Example
int id = 10;

static void show(){
    System.out.println(id); // ERROR
}
💡 Why?

❌ id belongs to object memory
❌ Static method belongs to class memory

No object exists yet.

🔷 11. Static Method → Static Method ✅
📌 Example
static void show(){
    print();
}

static void print(){
}
💡 Why?

✅ Both belong to class memory

🔷 12. Static Method → Static Variable ✅
📌 Example
static int count = 100;

static void show(){
    System.out.println(count);
}
💡 Why?

✅ Both stored in Method Area

⭐ MAIN POINT OF STATIC METHOD
✅ Static Method Can Access ONLY Static Members
✅ Static Variable
✅ Static Method
❌ Cannot Directly Access
❌ Instance Variable
❌ Instance Method
🔥 MEMORY ALLOCATION IN JAVA
📌 Example Program
class Student{

    int id = 101;
    static String college = "ABC";

    void show(){
        System.out.println(id);
        display();
    }

    static void display(){
        System.out.println(college);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args){

        Student s1 = new Student();

        s1.show();
    }
}
